--------------------------------------------------------------------------

 4.007 (24-Jul-2000)
 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
[*] Now you can refer from Freestyler to its Internet home page 
    [http://hres.narod.ru].
[-] Redefinition of Flags Folder took effect only after restart.
[*] Freestyler now would not process [exit.now], [nodelist.ok], 
    [password.ok], [dupovr.ok], and [ipovr.ok] flags created in its 
    Home Directory.
[+] Macroses for 'Execute' field (Config->Externals):
    %Exit% - exit the program;
    %CompileNodelist% - compile the nodelist;
    %OpenIP% - open TCP/IP Daemon;
    %CloseIP% - close TCP/IP Daemon;
    %ImportPasswordList% - import the list of passwords (similar to 
    Argus's [password.ok] flag);
    %ImportDialupNodesList% - import the list of Dial-up nodes overrides 
    (similar to Argus's [dupovr.ok] flag);
    %ImportIPNodesList% - import the list of TCP/IP nodes overrides
    (similar to Argus's [ipovr.ok] flag).
    The names of macroses are case-insensitive.
[+] Changed 'About' window.
[*] [open.Line] and [close.Line] flags now are to be created in the Flags 
    Folder. There also the mailer will create [active.Line] flags.
[*] [online.Line] flags (where Line - the line's name) are being created 
    in session time.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------

 4.006 (24-Jul-2000)
 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
[+] Added %NETMAIL% and %TIC% postprocessors' macroses.
[*] "Hot" F5 key for [AdvGrids]. Row addition.
    (Valera Loktionov 2:5097/36.27)
[+] Size of [fstyler.exe] file was decreased for 20 Kb by substitute
    of [seldir.pas] module for the single SHBrowseForFolder Win32API
    function.
[+] Flags are now placed in the separate folder. Define it in 
    Config->Paths.
    (Alexandr Sutulov 2:6083/3.1)
[!] Flags processing module has been entirely rebuilt. Now processing 
    is performed immediately on creation/removal of a flag (or with a 
    short delay), but not more often than once a second.
    (Alexandr Sutulov 2:6083/3.1)
[+] Format of flag names has been altered:
    flagname.flg - if the flag exists (created) then execute a command.
    ?flagname.flg - if the flag does not exist (deleted) then execute 
    a command.
    *flagname.flg - if the flag exists (created) then delete it and 
    execute a command.
    ?*flagname.flg - if the flag does not exist (deleted) then create 
    it and execute a command.
    (Oleg Redut 2:5000/111)
[*] The license agreement is put away.

